FBIS4-39304 "drsov109_a_94029" FBIS-SOV-94-109 Daily Report 4 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Paris Club Agrees To Defer Debt Repayments Paris Club Agrees To Defer Debt Repayments LD0406114794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0958 GMT 4 Jun 94 LD0406114794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikita Yermakov] [Text] Paris, 4 Jun -- An agreement on deferring seven billion dollars of Russia's foreign debt repayments this year was reached here today with representatives of the Paris Club which unites 19 creditor states. Russia's total foreign debt, inherited from the former Soviet Union, is approximately 80 billion dollars. Forty-five billion of this is owed to states belonging to the Paris Club.
